<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10134004>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Heads of Ancistrocerus species in frontal view. A, C. Ancistrocerus antilope (Panzer, 1798) from Crimea. B, D. Ancistrocerus capra (de Saussure, 1857) from New York State. A, B. Females. C, D. Males. Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10134004/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10134006>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Male genitalia of Ancistrocerus species. A, B, E, F. Ancistrocerus antilope (Panzer, 1798) from Crimea. C, D, G, H. Ancistrocerus capra (de Saussure, 1857) from Colorado. A, C. Left paramere and volsella, dorsal view. B, D. Left paramere and volsella, medial view. E, G. Aedeagus, dorsal view. F, H. Aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: aa = aedeagus apex; cl = cuspis lobe; d = digitus; vl = ventral lobe." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10134006/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

